The paper deals with solving Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs) using Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic Programming (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the experimental results of the proposed algorithm, which involves optimization and constraint satisfaction, making it relevant to the subfield of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-agent problems, which falls under the subfield of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper introduces a new algorithm based on logic programming, which is relevant to the subfield of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
